        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p><span>Your deity sends wracking plagues. The target must attempt a Fortitude save. When you Cast the Spell, decide whether the disease inflicts the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Clumsy]{Clumsy}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled}, or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stupefied]{Stupefied} condition.<br /><br /><strong>Divine Plague</strong> (disease) <strong>Level</strong> 1; </span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Stage 1</strong> Clumsy 1, Enfeebled 1, or Stupefied 1 (1 round); </span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Stage 2</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed} 1 and Clumsy 1, Enfeebled 1, or Stupefied 1 (1 round);</span></p>\n<p><span> <strong>Stage 3</strong> Clumsy 1, Enfeebled 1, or Stupefied 1 and the target can't recover from the condition until they are cured (1 day)<br /></span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span><strong>Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Failure</strong> The target is afflicted with divine plague at stage 1.</span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target is afflicted with divine plague at stage 2.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (5th)</strong> The divine plague disease gains the virulent trait. The condition value for the Clumsy, Enfeebled, or Stupefied condition is 2 instead of 1.</p>"
